{"tid":2039002,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"李嘉誠伊朗生意已被美國搶走","createTime":"2020-05-27T21:27:11.000Z","updateTime":"2020-05-28T05:32:31.000Z","uid":118550,"like":223,"dislike":52,"uniUserReply":90,"replies":[{"pid":"5861bf7acfc32c0d451b3f709c5f895863d34e2f","tid":2039002,"uid":118550,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-05-27T21:27:11.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-05-26/israel-s-ide-wins-tender-to-build-desalination-plant\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2020-05-26%2Fisrael-s-ide-wins-tender-to-build-desalination-plant&d=%2FAUJPsyZ5YTgQdLV7Kr5PugMmE0tIaoAQI%2BAeX1JER4%3D&h=87e71918\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-05-26/israel-s-ide-wins-tender-to-build-desalination-plant</a><br />\n<br />\nBloombergSubscribe<br />\nLi Ka-Shing Hong Kong Group Loses Israel Deal Amid U.S. Push<br />\nBy Shirley Zhao and Ivan Levingston, 26/5/2020 下午3:04:23<br />\nThe Hong Kong conglomerate founded by billionaire Li Ka-shing lost a bid for a major infrastructure project in Israel, weeks after the U.S. asked its Middle Eastern ally to review potential security threats posed by China-based companies.<br />\n<br />\nAn affiliate of CK Hutchison Holdings Ltd., the flagship of the tycoon&rsquo;s sprawling business empire, lost out on the contract to build and operate Israel&rsquo;s biggest desalination plant to IDE Technologies, a local company, the Israeli government said. In the past, Hutchison Water International Holdings Pte. had operated a desalination plant in the vicinity of the planned facility in partnership with IDE.<br />\n<br />\nIsrael&rsquo;s decision to choose a domestic bidder is the latest blow to Li&rsquo;s son and successor, CK Hutchison Chairman Victor Li, two years after his bid to buy a gas pipeline operator in Australia was blocked on national security concerns. Representatives for CK Hutchison in Hong Kong didn&rsqu